answers.body_markdown:
The problem in Edge is that [they do not support](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/FormData#Browser_compatibility) destructuring of FormData object. (`for ... of` in linked table).

Indeed, you are relying on this behavior from other browsers in your code, because `URLSearchParams( init )` constructor accepts a [*record*](https://heycam.github.io/webidl/#idl-record) as `init` parameter.  

[The specs](https://url.spec.whatwg.org/#concept-urlsearchparams-new) read

&gt; 3. Otherwise, if init is a record, then for each *name* → *value* in init, append a new name-value pair whose name is *name* and value is *value*, to query’s list. 

So this means that your code is actually doing

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-js --&gt;

    const formData = new FormData( searchForm );

    const urlParams = new URLSearchParams();
    for ( let [ name, value ] of formData ) {
      urlParams.append( name, value );
    }
    let formUrl = urlParams.toString();

    console.log( formUrl );

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    &lt;form id=&quot;searchForm&quot;&gt;
      &lt;input name=&quot;foo&quot; value=&quot;bar&quot;&gt;
      &lt;input name=&quot;baz&quot; value=&quot;bla&quot;&gt;
    &lt;/form&gt;

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

But since, once again, Edge doesn&#39;t support destructuring of FormData, your code breaks. 

However, according to MDN, they do support `for ... of FormData.entries()`, so maybe this would work (no Edge to test though so let me know).

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-js --&gt;

    let formUrl = new window.URLSearchParams(
      new window.FormData(this.searchForm)
        .entries() // explicitely call .entries() to get the iterator
    ).toString()

    console.log( formUrl );

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    &lt;form id=&quot;searchForm&quot;&gt;
      &lt;input name=&quot;foo&quot; value=&quot;bar&quot;&gt;
      &lt;input name=&quot;baz&quot; value=&quot;bla&quot;&gt;
    &lt;/form&gt;

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

